  "market_context": "The analyst presented two bull flag examples on a schematic candlestick chart to illustrate quality differences in pattern formation, focusing on the strength of the preceding impulsive move.",
  "key_observation": "The bull flag preceded by strong impulsive candles (large real bodies) is superior to the one preceded by small, low-momentum candles—even if the latter looks more textbook-like.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: The analyst identified two bull flag patterns on the chart—one with a sharp, strong impulsive move before the flag and another with a weaker, low-momentum upward move.",
    "Step 2: He compared the pre-flag momentum: the first had large green candles indicating strong buying pressure, while the second had many small candles suggesting weak conviction.",
    "Step 3: He concluded the flag with strong prior momentum is better, regardless of whether the flag itself has textbook lower highs/lows or appears as a simple tight pullback.",
    "Step 4: He emphasized that strong prior momentum increases the probability of a successful continuation breakout."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Prior momentum quality matters more than flag symmetry; strong impulsive moves before consolidation signal higher-probability continuation trades, while weak momentum suggests lack of institutional participation.",
